According to an article on Fox Business, small business optimism in the US reached a 35-year high in July 2018. The NFIB's Small Business Optimism Index reached its second highest level in its 45-year history, at 107.9. Job creation plans also set records, with a net 23 percent of businesses planning to create new jobs. However, businesses cited the availability of qualified workers as their biggest challenge, with 37 percent of owners reporting job openings that they could not fill. Despite this, small business owners expect better business conditions and are increasing compensation for workers.